Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and have the @lemon{1/2}(zested). Trim the @green beans{80%g}(trimmed and chopped into thirds).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the onion and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook the onion until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}, stir every minute or so. Once soft, stir in half the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @orzo{180%g}. Pour in the @water{450%ml} and the @vegetable stock powder{1}.

Stir the mixture together and bring to a simmer. Cook until the orzo is tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Stir regularly to stop it sticking to the bottom of the pan.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the beans and cook until slightly charred, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @king prawns{300%g} and remaining @garlic{1%clove}(grated) along with a splash of water. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and cook for ~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when opaque all the way through. Remove from the heat.

Once the orzo is cooked, remove from the heat.

> TIP: If the orzo is not quite cooked but the stock has been absorbed, just add a splash more water and keep cooking until it's tender.

Add the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, @harissa paste{50%g}, prawns, beans and a pinch of lemon zest. Stir together gently until well combined.

Add a squeeze of lemon to the orzo, taste and add more salt, pepper and lemon juice if you feel it needs it. Spoon into #bowls{} and finish with a sprinkle of lemon zest. Enjoy!

> Step 4 MOD: If you've chosen to get extra prawns, just cook the recipe in the same way. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.